This is a python code which is based on the ASE (atomistic structure enviroment).
It should help you to visualise SPRKKR structure as written in the Potential file
and in_structure.inp (semi-infinite surface) structural file as written by kkrspec.

Visualisation can be done by using ase enviroment. You can also export ASE supported 
files (cif, vasp, elk etc...) and visualise it e.g. by Vesta.

Easiest way is to work within ANACONDA python enviroment.


usage: visualise_in_struct.py [-h] [-i INPUT] -p POT [-o OUT] [-f FORMAT] [-a]
                              [-v VAC] [-b NBULK]

This is a sctipt to visualise in_struct.inp files. You can either use ase
visualisation tools or export it to cif file

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -i INPUT, --input INPUT
                        in_struct.inp file name (if not specified only pot
                        file will be ploted)
  -p POT, --pot POT     Filemane of scf Potential (always needed to be
                        specified)
  -o OUT, --out OUT     Output file name for structure (default strcuture.cif)
  -f FORMAT, --format FORMAT
                        Output file fomrmat for structure (see ase allowed
                        formats, default cif)
  -a, --ase             Use ase visualisation
  -v VAC, --vac VAC     Size of added vacuum in AA (default=10.0)
  -b NBULK, --nbulk NBULK
                        Repetition of bulk unit (default=2)



